We think that qualified majority voting is a guarantee of efficiency, and we think that codecision is a guarantee of democracy.
We would add that supervision by the Court of Justice is a guarantee of legal certainty.
MrÂ President, what is the Councilâs position in this case?
With the Treaties of Amsterdam and Nice, you have the legal option of implementing the extension.
